                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/2873½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State of a Conversation with
                        the Nicaraguan Minister</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Chamorro</hi>), <hi
                        rend="italic">May 25, 1922</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                        type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1922-05-25">May 25, 1922</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>The Minister called to express his appreciation of the action taken by the
                    American Minister in Nicaragua in quelling the recent revolution. <pb
                        facs="0864" n="750" xml:id="pg_750"/> The Minister thought that a very
                    serious outbreak would have occurred had it not been for the prompt action of
                    the American Minister. The Secretary said that this action had this Government’s
                    full approval.</p>
            </div>
